episodes.title: Ruveal: Meet the Queens
episodes.plot: Start your engines, racers. Willow Pill introduces the cast of RuPaul's Drag Race Season 15.

episodes.title: One Night Only, Pt. 1
episodes.plot: All-new queens make their debut in the werk room, kicking off Season 15 with a photo shoot and a musical number to introduce a talent show, and Ariana Grande returns to guest judge.

episodes.title: One Night Only, Pt. 2
episodes.plot: For the Season 15 premiere talent show, the queens flaunt their unique skills and then walk the runway in looks that show their personal styles, and pop superstar Ariana Grande guest judges.

episodes.title: All Queens Go to Heaven
episodes.plot: In this heavenly acting challenge, the queens must create infomercials for a queer afterlife. Country singer Maren Morris and LGBT activist Ts Madison guest judge.

episodes.title: Supersized Snatch Game
episodes.plot: Ru serves up a double helping of the celebrity impersonation game show, with the queens playing in two rounds, with two different casts of characters. Amandla Stenberg (The Hate U Give) guest judges.

episodes.title: House of Fashion
episodes.plot: The queens must turn home decor into haute couture; actress Janelle Monae guest judges.

episodes.title: Old Friends Gold
episodes.plot: The queens fast forward 50 years to perform in old lady girl groups, singing about life, love, and growing old with your besties. Actress/ comedian Megan Stalter (Hacks) guest judges.

episodes.title: The Daytona Wind 2
episodes.plot: The queens exchange flatulence for canned joy, as the melodramatic act challenge returns in surreal sitcom form; actor Harvey Guillén guest judges.

episodes.title: LipSync Lalaparuza Smackdown
episodes.plot: Strategy and alliances emerge as the queens face off in a series of lip syncs, all leading to a final sudden death elimination round.

episodes.title: The Crystal Ball: Episode 200
episodes.plot: In honor of Drag Race's 15th anniversary, the queens recreate memorable moments from the show and then walk the runway in three distinct looks for a ball, and Julia Garner guest judges.

episodes.title: 50/50's Most Gagworthy Stars
episodes.plot: The queens chat with Love Connie, Charo and Frankie Grande in celeb news interviews; have a runway renaissance for Night of a Thousand Beyonces and face guest judge Ts Madison.

episodes.title: Two Queens, One Joke
episodes.plot: The queens perform stand-up comedy in pairs, but an odd number of queens causes for some drama. Comedian Ali Wong (Ali Wong: Baby Cobra) guest judges.

episodes.title: Wigloose: The Rusical!
episodes.plot: The queens tell the story of rebellion as they put on a showstopping musical about a small town where bigots have outlawed the art of drag, and musician Orville Peck guest judges.

episodes.title: Teacher Makeovers
episodes.plot: The queens give drag makeovers to hard-working teachers, from kindergarten to high school. Queer pop musician Hayley Kiyoko guest judges.

episodes.title: Blame It on the Edit
episodes.plot: The final queens collab with RuPaul on a remix of his song "Blame It On The Edit," recording their own verses and creating a space-themed music video.

episodes.title: Reunited
episodes.plot: One week away from the Grand Finale, the queens return to discuss the season's gaggiest moments.

episodes.title: Grand Finale
episodes.plot: RuPaul crowns America's Next Drag Superstar.
